Block HTTP/HTTPS on EC2 Security Group (30 seconds)

Scenario:
Simulates a misconfigured Security Group that blocks inbound web traffic.

What breaks:
Inbound HTTP (80) and HTTPS (443) access to the EC2 web server
Application becomes unreachable from the browser

What restores:
Original Security Group rules are restored automatically after the chaos window

Target:
EC2 instance Security Group

Lambda used:
sg_chaos

Parameters (Environment Variables):

      TARGET_SG_ID=sg-xxxxxxxx
      CHAOS_DURATION_SECONDS=30
      STATE_BUCKET=chaos-monkey-state-yourname
